#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L03_Handshake
msgid "Handshake Lemma"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `theorem handshake_lemma (G : Graph) : sumDegrees G = 2 * edgeCount G`
#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L03_Handshake
msgid "The sum of the degrees of the vertices is twice the number of the edges in a graph.\n"
"§0"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `sumDegrees_addEdge (G : Graph) (e : Edge) (h : e ∉ G.E) : sumDegrees (addEdge G e)  = sumDegrees G + 2`
#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L02_AddEdge
msgid "§0\n"
"Adding one new edge increases the total degree sum by 2."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L03_Handshake
msgid "The total degree sum equals twice the number of edges.\n"
"\n"
"Prove it by induction on the number of edges."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `def sumDegrees (G : Graph) : Nat := G.V.sum (fun v => degree G v)`
#. §1: `degree`
#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L02_AddEdge
msgid "§0\n"
"The sum of the degrees of all the vertices in the graph. See definition of §1 for more."
msgstr ""

#. §0: ```
#. structure Edge where
#.   fst : Nat
#.   snd : Nat
#.   hne : fst ≠ snd
#. ```
#. §1: `(fst, snd)`
#. §2: `fst != snd`
#. §3: `fst`
#. §4: `snd`
#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L02_AddEdge
msgid "§0\n"
"Edges are ordered pairs of natural numbers §1 where §2.\n"
"§3 indicates the vertex the edge arises out of and §4 indicates the vertex the edge goes into."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L02_AddEdge
msgid "Adding One Edge"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L01_SingleEdge
msgid "An edge contributes 1 to the degree of each endpoint.\n"
"\n"
"How much does it contribute in total?"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L02_AddEdge
msgid "We know what happens to the total degree sum when we add an edge.\n"
"Use the helper lemma."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory
msgid "Four worlds have collapsed into one.\n"
"\n"
"Every theorem you prove reveals another clue in the murder mystery.\n"
"Work through graph theory from the Handshake Lemma all the way to Euler's theorem."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L01_SingleEdge
msgid "One Edge Contributes Two"
msgstr ""

#. §0: ```
#. structure Graph where
#.   V : Finset Nat
#.   E : Finset Edge
#. ```
#. §1: `(a, b)`
#. §2: `a != b`
#. §3: `G`
#. §4: `G.V`
#. §5: `G.E`
#: Game.Levels.GraphTheory.L02_AddEdge
msgid "§0\n"
"A graph is a set of vertices V (each vertex represented as a natural number) and a set of edges E\n"
"(each edge represented by an ordered pair §1 where §2. See the definition of Edge for more info)\n"
"\n"
"For a graph §3, you can access its vertex set so: §4, and its edge set so: §5."
msgstr ""

